1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:03,626
This is the judge’s place and this is his room

2
00:00:03,667 --> 00:00:06,417
We were transferred to him from the upper floor at noon

3
00:00:06,876 --> 00:00:11,959
Here there was a group of chairs

4
00:00:12,459 --> 00:00:16,292
On both sides, and here was the table. They made me sit here

5
00:00:16,751 --> 00:00:19,709
He asked me—How is your level in religion?

6
00:00:19,709 --> 00:00:22,375
I told him, I know, but I wasn’t praying. He said—Stand up and call the <i>adhan</i>

7
00:00:23,042 --> 00:00:27,000
I didn’t know it well and didn’t answer him well

8
00:00:27,626 --> 00:00:31,667
So he wrote that I had to learn how to pray

9
00:00:31,709 --> 00:00:37,167
They had a special room where they taught people every Wednesday and Saturday

10
00:00:37,417 --> 00:00:42,834
And also those whose identity papers they had would come too

11
00:00:43,250 --> 00:00:45,375
Interviewer: When they brought you into this room

12
00:00:45,459 --> 00:00:49,542
You must have seen them

13
00:00:50,334 --> 00:00:55,459
Was the judge Arab?

14
00:00:55,500 --> 00:00:58,375
And was his dialect from Mosul or did he speak standard Arabic?

15
00:00:58,542 --> 00:01:01,626
And about how old was the judge? Did you know him before?

16
00:01:01,626 --> 00:01:05,500
And the people who were in this room

17
00:01:05,626 --> 00:01:09,792
Did you know any of them? And about how old were they?

18
00:01:09,834 --> 00:01:14,459
And were their appearances from Mosul or from the villages or from outside Iraq?

19
00:01:14,709 --> 00:01:17,959
The judge was Arab, but not from Mosul

20
00:01:18,667 --> 00:01:21,751
And he had a young son

21
00:01:22,250 --> 00:01:27,417
He wore a gold watch, and it was known that this boy was the judge’s son

22
00:01:27,834 --> 00:01:30,500
When he came, people feared him

23
00:01:31,000 --> 00:01:34,876
Interviewer: How was his son wearing a gold watch when they forbid it?

24
00:01:34,918 --> 00:01:38,500
I don’t know, he would come and everyone knew him

25
00:01:38,626 --> 00:01:42,584
His son was young, thirteen or fourteen

26
00:01:43,709 --> 00:01:46,417
Interviewer: Who was the judge and how old was he?

27
00:01:46,417 --> 00:01:49,626
He was about forty-five years old

28
00:01:50,751 --> 00:01:54,876
Those who sat there were young and old

29
00:01:55,459 --> 00:01:58,334
Here sat four or five

30
00:01:58,334 --> 00:02:01,626
And here too, from their group

31
00:02:02,459 --> 00:02:05,834
Interviewer: Did anything change in this place or did it stay the same?

32
00:02:05,834 --> 00:02:09,626
No, it’s the same place. This opening wasn’t here

33
00:02:10,292 --> 00:02:15,751
And over there was a cupboard with shelves and items

34
00:02:16,209 --> 00:02:17,959
For the people, and this

35
00:02:18,125 --> 00:02:21,626
Interviewer: What was he wearing? Witness: Black clothes and a turban

36
00:02:22,459 --> 00:02:25,250
He had a beard, but it wasn’t long

37
00:02:25,375 --> 00:02:26,876
Interviewer: How was his manner with you?

38
00:02:26,876 --> 00:02:32,167
You know their manner and how they treat people

39
00:02:32,667 --> 00:02:36,959
Interviewer: Did he treat you harshly? Witness: Yes, somewhat

40
00:02:38,209 --> 00:02:40,834
Interviewer: You mean he ordered them to give you lessons?

41
00:02:40,834 --> 00:02:43,918
They gave me mandatory lessons

42
00:02:44,751 --> 00:02:47,626
Interviewer: How many days a week? Witness: Two days

43
00:02:47,876 --> 00:02:49,584
Saturday and Wednesday

44
00:02:49,709 --> 00:02:53,000
There was a room and a teaching board

45
00:02:53,042 --> 00:02:54,876
Interviewer: Was it like a school style?

46
00:02:54,876 --> 00:03:00,667
It was a classroom, and you had to learn and realize that they were fighting

47
00:03:00,959 --> 00:03:05,667
And their goal was to win you over to their side

48
00:03:06,125 --> 00:03:08,918
Interviewer: How many times did you appear before the judge?

49
00:03:08,918 --> 00:03:10,876
Three times
